  <li>
    <p>But I may <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="defy"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(谅[做不了后面的事])</code></b> even your sagacity to discover the name of your admirer.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>This young gentleman is blessed in a peculiar way, with everything <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="the heart of mortal can most desire"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(凡人之心所能渴望的)</code></b> – <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="splendid property, noble kindred, and extensive patronage"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(富丽堂皇的财产，高贵的家族，广阔的血统？)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Yet, in spite of all these tempatations, let me warn my cousin Elizabeth, and yourself, of <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="what evils you may incur by a precipitate closure with this gentleman's proposals"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(冒冒失失同意这位先生的求婚将会招致多大的祸害)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>But this perfect indifference and your <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="pointed"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(明显的)</code></b> dislike make it so delightedly absurd.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I shall not <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="sport with"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(拿...开玩笑)</code></b> your impatience by reading what he says on that point.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I am truly rejoiced that my cousin Lydia’s sad business had benen so well <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="hushed up"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(隐瞒/掩饰)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Your daughter Elizabeth, it is presumed, will not longer bear the name of Bennet, after her eldest sister has <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="resinged"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(放弃[姓氏])</code></b> it.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>We have reason to imagine that his aunt, Lady Catherine de Bourgh, does not <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="look on the match with a friendly eye"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(对这门婚姻不赞成)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Could he, or, the Lucases, have <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="pitched on"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(选出/选定)</code></b> any man, within the circle of our aquantance, whose name would have <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="give the lie more effectually to what they related; give the lie to sth - 证明...不实"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(更能证实他们所说的完全是子虚乌有的事)</code></b>?</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>You are not going to be <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="missish"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(耍小姐脾气/表现得小气)</code></b>, I hope, and pretend to be affronted at an idle report.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>For what do live, but to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="make sport for our neighbourhood"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(让邻居们一乐)</code></b>, and laugh at them in our turn?</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Nay, when I read a letter of his, I cannot help giving him the perference even over Wickham, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="much as"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(尽管)</code></b> I value the imprudence and hypocrisy of my son-in-law.</p>
